      Fn::Select:\n          - 1\n          - Fn::GetAZs: \"\"\n      CidrBlock: 10.0.3.0/24\n      MapPublicIpOnLaunch: false\n      Tags:\n        - Key: aws-cdk:subnet-name\n          Value: Private\n        - Key: aws-cdk:subnet-type\n          Value: Private\n        - Key: Name\n          Value: WorkshopStack/Vpc/WorkshopVpc/PrivateSubnet2\n      VpcId:\n        Ref: VpcWorkshopVpcAB7D061C\n  VpcWorkshopVpcPrivateSubnet2RouteTable9C677543:\n    Type: AWS::EC2::RouteTable\n    Properties:\n      Tags:\n        - Key: Name\n          Value: WorkshopStack/Vpc/WorkshopVpc/PrivateSubnet2\n      VpcId:\n        Ref: VpcWorkshopVpcAB7D061C\n  VpcWorkshopVpcPrivateSubnet2RouteTableAssociation541BD7CF:\n    Type: AWS::EC2::SubnetRouteTableAssociation\n    Properties:\n      RouteTableId:\n        Ref: VpcWorkshopVpcPrivateSubnet2RouteTable9C677543\n      SubnetId:\n        Ref: VpcWorkshopVpcPrivateSubnet2SubnetA1F06CF5\n  VpcWorkshopVpcPrivateSubnet2DefaultRoute7F56E125:\n    Type: AWS::EC2::Route\n    Properties:\n      DestinationCidrBlock: 0.0.0.0/0\n      NatGatewayId:\n        Ref: VpcWorkshopVpcPublicSubnet1NATGatewayB7F27960\n      RouteTableId:\n        Ref: VpcWorkshopVpcPrivateSubnet2RouteTable9C677543\n  VpcWorkshopVpcIGW19681F96:\n    Type: AWS::EC2::InternetGateway\n    Properties:\n      Tags:\n        - Key: Name\n          Value: workshop-vpc\n  VpcWorkshopVpcVPCGWBF8004A5:\n    Type: AWS::EC2::VPCGatewayAttachment\n    Properties:\n      InternetGatewayId:\n        Ref: VpcWorkshopVpcIGW19681F96\n      VpcId:\n        Ref: VpcWorkshopVpcAB7D061C\n  VpcWorkshopVpcRestrictDefaultSecurityGroupCustomResourceDD84FC6A:\n    Type: Custom::VpcRestrictDefaultSG\n    Properties:\n      ServiceToken:\n        Fn::GetAtt:\n          - CustomVpcRestrictDefaultSGCustomResourceProviderHandlerDC833E5E\n          - Arn\n      DefaultSecurityGroupId:\n        Fn::GetAtt:\n          - VpcWorkshopVpcAB7D061C\n          - DefaultSecurityGroup\n      Account:\n        Ref: AWS::AccountId\n    UpdateReplacePolicy: Delete\n    DeletionPolicy: Delete\n  CustomVpcRestrictDefaultSGCustomResourceProviderRole26592FE0:\n    Type: AWS::IAM::Role\n    Properties:\n      AssumeRolePolicyDocument:\n        Version: \"2012-10-17\"\n        Statement:\n          - Action: sts:AssumeRole\n            Effect: Allow\n            Principal:\n              Service: lambda.amazonaws.com\n      ManagedPolicyArns:\n        - Fn::Sub: arn:${AWS::Partition}:iam::aws:policy/service-role/AWSLambdaBasicExecutionRole\n      Policies:\n        - PolicyName: Inline\n          PolicyDocument:\n            Version: \"2012-10-17\"\n            Statement:\n              - Effect: Allow\n                Action:\n                  - ec2:AuthorizeSecurityGroupIngress\n                  - ec2:AuthorizeSecurityGroupEgress\n                  - ec2:RevokeSecurityGroupIngress\n                  - ec2:RevokeSecurityGroupEgress\n                Resource:\n                  - Fn::Join:\n                      - \"\"\n                      - - \"arn:\"\n                        - Ref: AWS::Partition\n                        - \":ec2:\"\n                        - Ref: AWS::Region\n                        - \":\"\n                        - Ref: AWS::AccountId\n                        - :security-group/\n                        - Fn::GetAtt:\n                            - VpcWorkshopVpcAB7D061C\n                            - DefaultSecurityGroup\n  CustomVpcRestrictDefaultSGCustomResourceProviderHandlerDC833E5E:\n    Type: AWS::Lambda::Function\n    Properties:\n      Code:\n        S3Bucket:\n          Fn::Sub: cdk-hnb659fds-assets-${AWS::AccountId}-${AWS::Region}\n        S3Key: 7fa1e366ee8a9ded01fc355f704cff92bfd179574e6f9cfee800a3541df1b200.zip\n      Timeout: 900\n      MemorySize: 128\n      Handler: __entrypoint__.handler\n      Role:\n        Fn::GetAtt:\n          - CustomVpcRestrictDefaultSGCustomResourceProviderRole26592FE0\n          - Arn\n      Runtime: nodejs22.x\n      Description: Lambda function for removing all inbound/outbound rules from the VPC default security group\n    DependsOn:\n      - CustomVpcRestrictDefaultSGCustomResourceProviderRole26592FE0\n    Metadata:\n      aws:asset:path: asset.7fa1e366ee8a9ded01fc355f704cff92bfd179574e6f9cfee800a3541df1b200\n      aws:asset:property: Code\n  IdeIdeBootstrapWaitConditionHandleEA0A1D15:\n    Type: AWS::CloudFormation::WaitConditionHandle\n  IdeIdeSecurityGroup5C503C8A:\n    Type: AWS::EC2::SecurityGroup\n    Properties:\n      GroupDescription: IDE security group\n      GroupName: ide-cloudfront-ide-sg\n      SecurityGroupEgress:\n        - CidrIp: 0.0.0.0/0\n          Description: Allow all outbound traffic by default\n          IpProtocol: \"-1\"\n      VpcId:\n        Ref: VpcWorkshopVpcAB7D061C\n  IdeIdeSecurityGroupfrompl3b927c5280C6D03D18:\n    Type: AWS::EC2::SecurityGroupIngress\n    Properties:\n      Description: HTTP from CloudFront only\n      FromPort: 80\n      GroupId:\n        Fn::GetAtt:\n          - IdeIdeSecurityGroup5C503C8A\n          - GroupId\n      IpProtocol: tcp\n      SourcePrefixListId: pl-3b927c52\n      ToPort: 80\n  IdeIdeInternalSecurityGroupD5D3B421:\n    Type: AWS::EC2::SecurityGroup\n    Properties:\n      GroupDescription: IDE internal security group\n      GroupName: ide-internal-sg\n      VpcId:\n        Ref: VpcWorkshopVpcAB7D061C\n  IdeIdeInternalSecurityGroupfromWorkshopStackIdeIdeInternalSecurityGroup236BB241ALLTRAFFIC024019C0:\n    Type: AWS::EC2::SecurityGroupIngress\n    Properties:\n      Description: Allow all internal traffic\n      GroupId:\n        Fn::GetAtt:\n          - IdeIdeInternalSecurityGroupD5D3B421\n          - GroupId\n      IpProtocol: \"-1\"\n      SourceSecurityGroupId:\n        Fn::GetAtt:\n          - IdeIdeInternalSecurityGroupD5D3B421\n          - GroupId\n  IdeIdeInternalSecurityGrouptoWorkshopStackIdeIdeInternalSecurityGroup236BB241ALLTRAFFIC65445F6E:\n    Type: AWS::EC2::SecurityGroupEgress\n    Properties:\n      Description: Allow all internal traffic\n      DestinationSecurityGroupId:\n        Fn::GetAtt:\n          - IdeIdeInternalSecurityGroupD5D3B421\n          - GroupId\n      GroupId:\n        Fn::GetAtt:\n          - IdeIdeInternalSecurityGroupD5D3B421\n          - GroupId\n      IpProtocol: \"-1\"\n  IdeIdeInstanceProfile8BD997EA:\n    Type: AWS::IAM::InstanceProfile\n    Properties:\n      InstanceProfileName:\n        Ref: RolesWorkshopRoleBD50F06E\n      Roles:\n        - Ref: RolesWorkshopRoleBD50F06E\n  IdeIdeElasticIP8B8439E1:\n    Type: AWS::EC2::EIP\n    Properties:\n      Domain: vpc\n  IdeLauncherFunctionBB1ABE05:\n    Type: AWS::Lambda::Function\n    Properties:\n      Code:\n        ZipFile: |-\n          import json\n          import boto3\n          import logging\n          from typing import Dict, List, Any, Optional\n\n          logger = logging.getLogger()\n          logger.setLevel(logging.INFO)\n\n          def lambda_handler(event: Dict[str, Any], context: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n              \"\"\"\n              EC2 instance launching Lambda function with multi-AZ and multi-instance-type failover.\n              Provides robust instance launching with automatic failover across availability zones\n              and instance types when capacity is not available.\n              \"\"\"\n              try:\n                  logger.info(f\"Received event: {json.dumps(event, default=str)}\")\n\n                  ec2 = boto3.client('ec2')\n\n                  # Extract and validate parameters\n                  ami_id = event.get('ImageId')\n                  subnet_ids = _parse_comma_separated(event.get('SubnetIds', ''))\n                  instance_types = _parse_comma_separated(event.get('InstanceTypes', 't3.medium'))\n                  security_group_ids = _parse_comma_separated(event.get('SecurityGroupIds', ''))\n                  instance_profile_arn = event.get('IamInstanceProfileArn')\n                  volume_size = int(event.get('VolumeSize', 20))\n                  instance_name = event.get('InstanceName', 'workshop-instance')\n                  user_data = event.get('UserData', '')\n\n                  # Validation\n                  if not ami_id:\n                      raise ValueError(\"ImageId is required\")\n                  if not subnet_ids:\n                      raise ValueError(\"At least one SubnetId is required\")\n                  if not security_group_ids:\n                      raise ValueError(\"At least one SecurityGroupId is required\")\n\n                  # Try each combination of subnet and instance type\n                  last_error = None\n                  for subnet_id in subnet_ids:\n                      for instance_type in instance_types:\n                          try:\n                              logger.info(f\"Attempting to launch {instance_type} in subnet: {subnet_id}\")\n\n                              launch_params = {\n                                  'ImageId': ami_id,\n                                  'MinCount': 1,\n                                  'MaxCount': 1,\n                                  'InstanceType': instance_type,\n                                  'SubnetId': subnet_id,\n                                  'SecurityGroupIds': security_group_ids,\n                                  'UserData': user_data,\n                                  'BlockDeviceMappings': [{\n                                      'DeviceName': '/dev/xvda',\n                                      'Ebs': {\n                                          'VolumeSize': volume_size,\n                                          'VolumeType': 'gp3',\n                                          'DeleteOnTermination': True\n                                      }\n                                  }],\n                                  'TagSpecifications': [{\n                                      'ResourceType': 'instance',\n                                      'Tags': [\n                                          {'Key': 'Name', 'Value': instance_name},\n                                          {'Key': 'Workshop', 'Value': 'true'}\n                                      ]\n                                  }]\n                              }\n\n                              if instance_profile_arn:\n                                  launch_params['IamInstanceProfile'] = {'Arn': instance_profile_arn}\n\n                              response = ec2.run_instances(**launch_params)\n                              instance = response['Instances'][0]\n                              instance_id = instance['InstanceId']\n\n                              logger.info(f\"Successfully launched {instance_type} instance: {instance_id} in {subnet_id}\")\n\n                              return {\n                                  'InstanceId': instance_id,\n                                  'InstanceType': instance_type,\n                                  'SubnetId': subnet_id,\n                                  'AvailabilityZone': instance['Placement']['AvailabilityZone'],\n                                  'Status': 'SUCCESS'\n                              }\n\n                          except Exception as launch_error:\n                              error_msg = str(launch_error)\n                              logger.warning(f\"Failed to launch {instance_type} in {subnet_id}: {error_msg}\")\n                              last_error = launch_error\n\n                              # Check if it's a capacity issue and continue to next combination\n                              if any(phrase in error_msg.lower() for phrase in [\n                                  'insufficient capacity', 'capacity not available',\n                                  'unsupported', 'invalid instance type'\n                              ]):\n                                  continue\n                              else:\n                                  # For other errors, still try other combinations but log more details\n                                  logger.error(f\"Non-capacity error for {instance_type} in {subnet_id}: {error_msg}\")\n                                  continue\n\n                  # If we get here, all combinations failed\n                  raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to launch instance with any combination of subnets {subnet_ids} \"\n                                    f\"and instance types {instance_types}. Last error: {str(last_error)}\")\n\n              except Exception as e:\n                  logger.error(f\"Error launching instance: {str(e)}\")\n                  # Re-raise the exception to signal CloudFormation stack failure\n                  # This is critical - if we can't launch the instance, the entire deployment is pointless\n                  raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to launch workshop instance: {str(e)}\")\n\n          def _parse_comma_separated(value: str) -> List[str]:\n              \"\"\"Parse comma-separated string into list, handling empty strings.\"\"\"\n              if not value or not value.strip():\n                  return []\n              return [item.strip() for item in value.split(',') if item.strip()]\n      FunctionName: ide-launcher\n      Handler: index.lambda_handler\n      Role:\n        Fn::GetAtt:\n          - RolesLambdaRole72F9D2A4\n          - Arn\n      Runtime: python3.13\n      Timeout: 300\n    DependsOn:\n      - RolesLambdaRoleDefaultPolicy90D67672\n      - RolesLambdaRole72F9D2A4\n  IdeLauncherFunctionLogGroup1867C7DB:\n    Type: AWS::Logs::LogGroup\n    Properties:\n      LogGroupName:\n        Fn::Join:\n          - \"\"\n          - - /aws/lambda/\n            - Ref: IdeLauncherFunctionBB1ABE05\n      RetentionInDays: 731\n    UpdateReplacePolicy: Retain\n    DeletionPolicy: Retain\n  IdeIdeEC2InstanceResource17A0C9F7:\n    Type: AWS::CloudFormation::CustomResource\n    Properties:\n      ServiceToken:\n        Fn::GetAtt:\n          - IdeLauncherFunctionBB1ABE05\n          - Arn\n      InstanceName: ide\n      InstanceTypes: m5.xlarge,m6i.xlarge,t3.xlarge\n      UserData:\n        Fn::Base64:\n          Fn::Join:\n            - \"\"\n            - - |-\n                #!/bin/bash\n                #!/bin/bash\n                set -e\n\n                # Generate unique log group name with runtime timestamp\n                L\n   </content>\n   </file>"
    },
