      "content": "CONTEXT TRANSFER: We are continuing a conversation that had gotten too long. Here is a summary:\n\n---\n## TASK 1: Create Infrastructure Refactoring Specification\n- **STATUS**: done\n- **USER QUERIES**: 1 (\"read refactoring.md and create specs for new infra\")\n- **DETAILS**: Created comprehensive spec with requirements, design, and tasks for migrating from current `infrastructure/` to new unified `infra/` approach. Used convention-based CDK deployment with single codebase generating multiple workshop templates.\n- **FILEPATHS**: `.kiro/specs/infra/requirements.md`, `.kiro/specs/infra/design.md`, `.kiro/specs/infra/tasks.md`, `.kiro/specs/infra/refactoring-to-new-infra.md`\n\n## TASK 2: Infrastructure Setup (1.x Tasks)\n- **STATUS**: done  \n- **USER QUERIES**: 2 (\"implement 1.x\")\n- **DETAILS**: Completed all infrastructure setup tasks including directory structure, CDK project initialization with Java 25 and CDK 2.215.0, and common script utilities with emoji-based logging.\n- **FILEPATHS**: `infra/` directory structure, `infra/cdk/pom.xml`, `infra/cdk/cdk.json`, `infra/cdk/src/main/java/sample/com/WorkshopApp.java`, `infra/scripts/lib/common.sh`, `infra/scripts/lib/wait-for-resources.sh`\n\n## TASK 3: Build System (2.x Tasks)  \n- **STATUS**: done\n- **USER QUERIES**: 3 (\"build sync cdk\")\n- **DETAILS**: Created template generation and sync scripts. Build system generates single CloudFormation template (`workshop-template.yaml`) and syncs to workshop directories. Includes npm automation scripts and policy copying from single source (`infra/cdk/src/main/resources/iam-policy.json`).\n- **FILEPATHS**: `infra/scripts/cfn/generate.sh`, `infra/scripts/cfn/sync.sh`, `infra/package.json`, `infra/cdk/src/main/resources/iam-policy.json`\n\n## TASK 4: Base IDE Stack (10.x Tasks)\n- **STATUS**: done\n- **USER QUERIES**: 4 (\"continue\")\n- **DETAILS**: Created core CDK constructs (Roles, Vpc, Ide, CodeBuild) and base workshop setup scripts. Successfully generates CloudFormation template with VPC, IDE instance, IAM roles, and CodeBuild project. Convention-based script discovery implemented. Tasks 10.1, 10.2, 10.3, 10.7, 10.8, 10.9, 10.10 completed.\n- **FILEPATHS**: `infra/cdk/src/main/java/sample/com/constructs/`, `infra/cdk/src/main/java/sample/com/stacks/WorkshopStack.java`, `infra/scripts/setup/`, `infra/scripts/workshops/`\n\n## TASK 5: Lambda Function Architecture Optimization\n- **STATUS**: done\n- **USER QUERIES**: 17 (\"problem. we cannot use java based lambda because it require jar and we cannot have jar in cfn. what to do?\"), 18 (\"yes, use python with source code in resources\"), 19 (\"unify and select concise names for lambdas\"), 20 (\"secret is used in IDE, check current implementation if we can\"), 21 (\"update specs and implement\")\n- **DETAILS**: \n  - **Analysis Phase**: Analyzed 5 Python Lambda functions and identified 3 that could be replaced with native CDK implementations\n  - **Optimization**: Reduced from 5 → 2 Lambda functions (60% reduction):\n    - **Removed**: `prefix.py` (replaced with static CloudFront prefix list `pl-3b927c52`), `password.py` (replaced with native CDK secret reference), `database.py` (moved to setup scripts)\n    - **Improved**: `launcher.py` (enhanced multi-AZ/instance-type failover), `bootstrap.py` (enhanced SSM execution)\n  - **CloudFormation Failure Handling**: Fixed both Lambda functions to properly raise exceptions instead of returning failure status, ensuring CloudFormation stack fails when critical components fail\n- **FILEPATHS**: `infra/cdk/src/main/resources/lambda/launcher.py`, `infra/cdk/src/main/java/sample/com/constructs/Ide.java`, `infra/cdk/src/main/java/sample/com/constructs/Roles.java`\n\n## TASK 6: Bootstrap Architecture Refactoring to User Data + GitHub\n- **STATUS**: in-progress\n- **USER QUERIES**: 22 (\"check properly the original implementation with boostraps,. ide sh, and bootsrap partds in stecks. it used ssm properly\"), 23 (\"can User Data clone github and run scripts from cloned?\"), 24 (\"yes, it looks appropriate. we neww to have bootstrap.sh in /Users/bezsonov/sources/workshops/java-on-aws/infra/scripts/setup instead of resources\")\n- **DETAILS**: \n  - **Completed**: \n    - Analyzed original SSM implementation with CloudWatch agent logging\n    - Eliminated bootstrap Lambda function entirely\n    - Eliminated SSM document approach\n    - Created dummy bootstrap script at `infra/scripts/setup/ide.sh` with CloudWatch agent logging (like original)\n    - Refactored IDE construct to use User Data + GitHub approach\n    - User Data clones GitHub repo and executes setup script with fallback mechanism\n    - Proper CloudFormation wait condition signaling\n  - **Current State**: Template generates successfully with only 1 Lambda function (launcher) + 1 CDK internal function\n  - **Architecture**: EC2 User Data → Clone GitHub → Execute `infra/scripts/setup/ide.sh` → CloudWatch logging → Signal completion\n- **NEXT STEPS**:\n  - Test the actual deployment to verify User Data + GitHub approach works\n  - Update GitHub repository URL from placeholder to actual repository\n  - Enhance bootstrap script from dummy version to full IDE setup\n  - Validate CloudWatch agent logging works correctly\n- **FILEPATHS**: `infra/scripts/setup/ide.sh`, `infra/cdk/src/main/java/sample/com/constructs/Ide.java`, `infra/cdk/src/main/resources/lambda/launcher.py`\n\n## USER CORRECTIONS AND INSTRUCTIONS:\n- Use Java 25 instead of Java 21 throughout the project\n- Use CDK version 2.215.0 instead of 2.167.1  \n- Use \"infra\" consistently instead of \"workshop-infrastructure\"\n- Default workshop type should be \"ide\" (VPC + IDE only)\n- Use bash scripts instead of TypeScript/JavaScript for build automation\n- Use jenv for Java version management on macOS\n- Workshop directories should be in same parent directory with matching names\n- Use emoji-based logging consistently in all scripts\n- Numbering strategy: 1.x setup, 2.x build, 10.x base IDE, 100.x+ workshops, 1000.x validation\n- Don't add useless comments like \"Replaces multiple Python/JavaScript Lambda functions\"\n- Don't use `@SuppressWarnings(\"unchecked\")` suppressions - use proper type-safe casting\n- Use Python Lambda functions with inline source code instead of Java (CloudFormation compatibility)\n- Have single source of truth for iam-policy.json in `infra/cdk/src/main/resources/`\n- Remove cfn folder - generate `workshop-template.yaml` directly in infra root\n- Use User Data + GitHub approach instead of SSM for bootstrap\n- Bootstrap script should be in `infra/scripts/setup/ide.sh` not resources\n- Include CloudWatch agent logging like original implementation\n- Lambda functions must raise exceptions (not return failure status) to fail CloudFormation stack\n\n## Files to read:\n- `infra/scripts/setup/ide.sh`\n- `infra/cdk/src/main/java/sample/com/constructs/Ide.java`\n- `infra/cdk/src/main/resources/lambda/launcher.py`\n- `infra/workshop-template.yaml`\n- `.kiro/specs/infra/tasks.md`\n\nUSER QUERIES (chronological order):\n1. names al not consise#### Python Source Organization```infra/cdk/src/main/resources/lambda/├── prefix.py      # CloudFront prefix list retrieval├── launcher.py    # EC2 instance launching with failover├── password.py    # Secrets Manager password retrieval├── bootstrap.py   # IDE instance bootstrap via SSM└── database.py    # Database setup and configuration you didn't finish with design/tasks update\n2. reread properly, too many mistakes | Old Function Name Pattern | New Source File | New Function Name | Scope | Purpose ||---------------------------|-----------------|-------------------|-------|---------|| `{instance}-prefix-list-lambda` | `prefix.py` | `{instance}-prefix` | Instance | CloudFront prefix list || `{instance}-instance-launcher` | `launcher.py` | `{instance}-launcher` | Instance | EC2 instance launching || `{instance}-password-lambda` | `password.py` | `{instance}-password` | Instance | Secrets Manager retrieval || `{instance}-bootstrap-lambda` | `bootstrap.py` | `{instance}-bootstrap` | Instance | IDE bootstrap via SSM || `unicornstore-db-setup-lambda` | `database.py` | `workshop-database` | Workshop | Database setup |#### Python Source Organization```infra/cdk/src/main/resources/lambda/├── prefix.py      # CloudFront prefix list├── launch.py      # EC2 instance launching├── secret.py      # Secrets Manager retrieval├── setup.py       # IDE bootstrap via SSM└── db.py          # Database setup\n3. prious table was correct, Python Source Organization wan't\n4. <kiro-ide-message> \n      Kiro IDE applied Autofix or formatted the following files and the file content was updated.\n      If you need to update these file, read them again.\n      Updated Files:\n      .kiro/specs/infra/design.md/n.kiro/specs/infra/tasks.md\n      \n      </kiro-ide-message>\n5. implement lambdas and ide\n6. iam-policy.json have it in one place for IDE and for sync and copy exect file from infrastructure\n7. not copy, have one location in resources\n8. do we need cfn folder for one file? is stack name ok?\n9. continue\n10. sysnc specs with implementation\n11. no need to do sysnc antil we funished. add this soimehwre, annoying, i told you several times\n12. <kiro-ide-message> \n      Kiro IDE applied Autofix or formatted the following files and the file content was updated.\n      If you need to update these file, read them again.\n      Updated Files:\n      .kiro/specs/infra/design.md/n.kiro/specs/infra/tasks.md\n      \n      </kiro-ide-message>\n13. recheck all new python lambdas and unify tehir code to the standards whcih we discuess and improve. there is not need to just copy, they need to be unified and better. but event more important, analys them adn decide if some can be dropped and replaced with native cdk implemeytation. analyse and explaine me proposal first\n14. secret is used in IDE, check current implementation if we can\n15. update specs and implement\n16. <kiro-ide-message> \n      Kiro IDE applied Autofix or formatted the following files and the file content was updated.\n      If you need to update these file, read them again.\n      Updated Files:\n      .kiro/specs/infra/design.md/n.kiro/specs/infra/tasks.md/ninfra/cdk/src/main/java/sample/com/constructs/Ide.java\n      \n      </kiro-ide-message>\n17. if launche fail to deploy instance we need to send cfn error to stop deployment, because the rest of deployment is pointless. do we do it?\n18. <kiro-ide-message> \n      Kiro IDE applied Autofix or formatted the following files and the file content was updated.\n      If you need to update these file, read them again.\n      Updated Files:\n      infra/cdk/src/main/resources/lambda/launcher.py/ninfra/cdk/src/main/resources/lambda/bootstrap.py\n      \n      </kiro-ide-message>\n19. do both sript iue consitent approach?\n20. what script executes bootsrap?\n21. check properly the original implementation with boostraps,. ide sh, and bootsrap partds in stecks. it used ssm properly\n22. bootstrap-script sript in name is redundate. is SSM the only way?\n23. <kiro-ide-message> \n      Kiro IDE applied Autofix or formatted the following files and the file content was updated.\n      If you need to update these file, read them again.\n      Updated Files:\n      infra/cdk/src/main/java/sample/com/constructs/Ide.java\n      \n      </kiro-ide-message>\n24. can User Data clone github and run scripts from cloned?\n25. infra/scripts/setup/ide.sh, more logical.\n26. <kiro-ide-message> \n      Kiro IDE applied Autofix or formatted the following files and the file content was updated.\n      If you need to update these file, read them again.\n      Updated Files:\n      infra/cdk/src/main/java/sample/com/constructs/Ide.java\n      \n      </kiro-ide-message>\n---\n\nMETADATA:\nThe previous conversation had 38 messages.\n\nINSTRUCTIONS:\nContinue working until the user query has been fully addressed. Do not ask for clarification - proceed with the work based on the context provided.\nIMPORTANT: you need to read from the files to Read section\n\n<EnvironmentContext>\nThis information is provided as context about user environment. Only consider it if it's relevant to the user request ignore it otherwise.\n\n<OPEN-EDITOR-FILES>\n<file name=\".kiro/specs/infra/requirements.md\" />\n<file name=\".kiro/specs/infra/design.md\" />\n<file name=\".kiro/specs/infra/tasks.md\" />\n<file name=\"infra/scripts/setup/ide.sh\" />\n<file name=\"infra/cdk/src/main/java/sample/com/constructs/Ide.java\" />\n<file name=\"infra/cdk/src/main/resources/lambda/launcher.py\" />\n</OPEN-EDITOR-FILES>\n\n<ACTIVE-EDITOR-FILE>\n<file name=\"infra/scripts/setup/ide.sh\" />\n</ACTIVE-EDITOR-FILE>\n</EnvironmentContext>"
