      "content": "You're absolutely right to question this! Let me explain the failure scenarios and why **EC2 Spot Fleet** is indeed the better solution.\n\n## Auto Scaling Group Failure Scenarios\n\n**❌ When Auto Scaling Group WILL Fail CloudFormation:**\n\n1. **All instance types unavailable in ALL AZs**: If `m5.xlarge`, `m6i.xlarge`, AND `t3.xlarge` have no capacity in BOTH AZs\n2. **Service limits exceeded**: Account limits for EC2 instances\n3. **Invalid configuration**: Wrong AMI, security groups, etc.\n\n**⚠️ Auto Scaling Group Behavior:**\n- ASG will keep retrying for ~15 minutes during CloudFormation creation\n- If it can't launch ANY instance after timeout → CloudFormation FAILS\n- But it's less intelligent than our current Lambda (which tries each combination systematically)\n\n## Better Solution: EC2 Spot Fleet\n\n**✅ Why Spot Fleet is Superior:**\n\n1. **Intelligent Failover**: Tries all combinations of instance types × AZs systematically\n2. **Immediate Failure**: Fails fast if no capacity available (like our Lambda)\n3. **Native AWS Service**: No custom Lambda needed\n4. **Cost Effective**: Can use Spot pricing with On-Demand fallback\n5. **Single Instance**: Perfect for our use case (we only need 1 IDE instance)\n\nLet me implement the Spot Fleet solution:"
